 needed to exhaust it by star formation. This suggests\nthat the nuclear outflow is one of the main quenching engines at work in the\nobserved suppression of the central star-formation activity in zC400528.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Jul 2018 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 21 Jul 2018 22:13:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-30"}
